South African Wheat Planting May Increase 7.2% on Higher Prices

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-04-20T13:30:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/south-african-wheat-planting-may-increase-7-2-on-higher-prices.html
South African farmers may increase
wheat plantings 7.2 percent this year after prices for the grain
improved.  Plantings may increase to 598,500 hectares (1.47 million
acres) from 558,100 hectares last year, Marda Scheepers, a
spokeswoman for the committee, said by phone from  Pretoria 
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
